tp:treatment-sec.p:

Charinus bordoni

was found only inside caves in the aphotic zone which, in combination with the complete absence of eyes, indicates it a troglobitic species (
Ravelo 1977
; 
Delle Cave 1986
).

Patronym honoring Dr Antônio D. Brescovit (
Giupponi & Miranda 2016
).

p.tp:material-citation:
Holotype BRAZIL • ♀ ; Amazonas , Piaçaba , Araçá River ; [ 00°25′17.75″ S , 62°54′30.24″ W ];
18 May 1982
; B. Mascarenhas leg.; IBSP 149 .

tp:treatment-sec.p:
Noun refering to the habitat of the species, bromeliads (
Jocqué & Giupponi 2012
).

